name: acq_complete
doc: The :ACQuire:COMPlete command affects the operation of the :DIGitize command. It specifies the minimum completion criteria for an acquisition.

name: acq_count
doc: Number of averages when acquisition mode is AVER

name: acq_mode
doc: Configures acquisition to real-time or segmented

name: acq_points
doc: Returns the number of points the hardware will acquire from the input signal. This is not directly controllable

name: chan_bwlimit
doc: Limit the badwidth of the channel

name: chan_coupling
doc: DC or AC input coupling of the channel

name: chan_display
doc: Turn on or off the channel display

name: display_annotate
doc: ASCII string to display on the oscillosocope

name: display_data
doc: Download screenshot from the oscilloscope. Format options are forced to PNG and Color

name: inksaver
doc: Invert graticule colors (change background to white)

name: time_pos
doc: Time for the trigger event to the display reference point

name: time_reference
doc: One division from the left, center, or one division from the right

name: time_vernier
doc: Turn on or off fine adjustment

name: waveform_points
doc: Set the number of points to be transferred

name: waveform_points_mode
doc: The :WAVeform:POINts:MODE command sets the data record to be transferred with the :WAVeform:DATA? query

name: is_running
doc: Check operation status register for if oscilloscope is running
